We currently rely on the ArcGIS hitTest() implementation and do not define an additional pixel tolerance in UPMAP. The getPrioritizedSharedHitTest() logic only prioritizes the returned results for overlapping geojson-layer assets. If needed, we could implement our own tolerance using a screen area or rectangle around the click point, but at this point it sounds like this was primarily a question about how ArcGIS hit testing works rather than a reported issue.